This program that simulates the Monty Hall problem and use it to estimate the
probability of winning if you stick and if you switch.

Result:
    change strategy: False
    n: 100
    result: 0.36
    change strategy: False
    n: 1000
    result: 0.344
    change strategy: False
    n: 10000
    result: 0.3284
    change strategy: False
    n: 1000000
    result: 0.33296
    change strategy: True
    n: 100
    result: 0.68
    change strategy: True
    n: 1000
    result: 0.677
    change strategy: True
    n: 10000
    result: 0.6652
    change strategy: True
    n: 1000000
    result: 0.667372

See http://wikipedia.org/wiki/Monty_Hall_problem
